dcterms:description: A grid-based environment where the agent navigates through a grid with walls, aiming to reach a goal state while dealing with stochastic movement.
dcterms:title: Gridworlds

dcterms:creator: T. Schaul
J. Quan
I. Antonoglou
D. Silver
dcterms:description: A toy example where the agent must navigate a series of states with two actions: advance or return, receiving a reward upon reaching the final state.
dcterms:title: Cliffwalk

dcterms:description: A discretized version of a continuous control task where the agent must swing up a pendulum and maintain it in an upright position.
dcterms:title: InvertedPendulum

dcterms:description: A discretized version of a continuous control task where the agent must push a vehicle up a steep hill by swinging back and forth to gain momentum.
dcterms:title: MountainCar

dcterms:description: A sparse graph environment with randomly drawn edges, where each state has two edges corresponding to actions, and one state is designated as the goal.
dcterms:title: SparseGraph

dcterms:creator: M. Plappert

dcterms:description: A set of continuous control tasks including HalfCheetah-v2, Hopper-v2, and Ant-v2, designed for evaluating reinforcement learning algorithms in complex environments.
dcterms:title: MuJoCo tasks (HalfCheetah-v2, Hopper-v2, Ant-v2)
